list.item:
Ask yourself "What is the problem?" You've got to get to the root of it. First ask yourself what you don't like about yourself. Then go deeper; 

why don't you like this aspect of yourself;

when did it start to occur;

how did you come to this conclusion?

When you ask yourselves these questions, you get to the root of it and you will be able to tackle it from there.EG: I think I'm too fat; because I can't fit into my clothes and guys  don't like me; it started when I told a guy I liked him but he turned me  down; He likes athletic girls so he must not like me because I am fat.
